Hi,
I'm trying to add a Repeater, and save as JSON column but it doesn't seem to work.
It save and there is no error, but once the page is refreshed there is nothing in the UI and phpMyAdmin.

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3c2b4aaa-73ae-4289-a79d-c29efedc7254)

NovaServiceProvider.php:
```php
NovaSettings::addSettingsFields([
    Repeater::make('FAQ', 'faq')
        ->repeatables([
            FaqItem::make()->confirmRemoval(),
        ])
        ->asJson(),
]);
```

FaqItem.php:
```php
class FaqItem extends Repeatable
{
    public function fields(NovaRequest $request): array
    {
        return [
            Text::make('Question', 'question'),
            Textarea::make('Answer', 'answer'),
        ];
    }
}
```

Any chance to add support for [Nova Tab Panels](https://nova.laravel.com/docs/v5/releases#tab-panels)?

They were introduced in Nova 5 as a replacement to the `eminiarts/nova-tabs` package and they have almost identical API and look.

Right now tabs are not appearing.

**EDIT**: It turns out it is implemented but you MUST pass a name to the Tab group otherwise it won't render.

For example this **will not work**
```php
Tab::group(fields: [
    Tab::make('Tab A', [
        /* fields here */
    ]),
    Tab::make('Tab B', [
        /* fields here */
    ])
])
```

but this will work just fine
```php
Tab::group('My tabs', [
    Tab::make('Tab A', [
        /* fields here */
    ]),
    Tab::make('Tab B', [
        /* fields here */
    ])
])
```

I have installed outl1ne/nova-settings "^5.2" into  Laravel 10 / nova 4.27 app and with default config
file config/nova-settings.php :

```
<?php

return [

    /**
     * Set a name for the settings table
